body:
Intro into who he was.

He was born in Seoul, South Korea on December thirtieth, nineteen ninety-five to two very loving parents. He was the second oldest in a family of three boys and one girl.

They moved to the United States of America when he was seven and somehow made their way to Texas a few years ago.

I met him in September 2018 on a bad day. I knocked over a display of books and he helped me clean them up and well…it just went from there.

He was kind hearted and sweet; an absolute menace at board games and a giant dork, but he was my dork. He couldn’t carry a tune to save his live, but he would still belt out everything at the top of his lungs. He was ARMY. He followed BTS on twitter before their debut and he had met them multiple times. He had pictures of himself with them that I have no access to at the moment or I’d put them here. He would tell me on a daily basis who in BTS (and occasionally other idol groups) he was going to leave me for. His bias was Jimin.

He was in Seoul for business and his family were in Seoul for the New Year and visiting his sick grandmother when the accident happened. I’ll talk about it another time I can’t right now.

The URL comes from a conversation he and I had over BTS.

“-𝒕𝒐 𝒍𝒊𝒗𝒆 𝒘𝒊𝒕𝒉 𝒂 𝒃𝒆𝒕𝒕𝒆𝒓 𝒉𝒆𝒂𝒓𝒕, 𝒂 𝒉𝒂𝒑𝒑𝒊𝒆𝒓 𝒉𝒆𝒂𝒓𝒕, 𝒕𝒉𝒊𝒔 𝒖𝒍𝒕𝒊𝒎𝒂𝒕𝒆𝒍𝒚, 𝒊𝒔 𝒕𝒉𝒆 𝒔𝒕𝒂𝒓𝒕𝒊𝒏𝒈 𝒑𝒐𝒊𝒏𝒕 𝒐𝒇 𝒆𝒗𝒆𝒓𝒚𝒕𝒉𝒊𝒏𝒈” ⁽ᴿᴹ ᴸᵒᵍ ²⁰¹⁸⁾
✿ ʟ-αяму 𝟐𝟑 · 𝐅
